    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Isn't this default behaviour [here](https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/master/packages/lodestar/src/sync/index.ts#L97)?\r\n\r\nThere may be an edge case, where the chain is lets say 9 months ahead at slot 10,000 (lol) and by the time we get to 10,000 the chain is at 15,000. 5000 block may be too much to regular sync, so an optimization would be to sync chunks (via get_blocks_by_range) from a bunch of different peers, put them in the queue (i believe the priority queue will handle this by default) and then wait until the queue finishes, then start regular sync.\r\n\r\nWriting this i realized that its because of the queue, that regular sync starts... lol\r\nWe need to be notified when the priority queue is empty...\r\n\r\nAlso addressed by #479 ",
